r142 | shannonmitchell | 2012-04-08 21:31:19 -0400 (Sun, 08 Apr 2012) | 10 lines


  - Created GEN000000-LNX001433 script for RHEL 6.  RHEL 6 has changed the default permissions of /etc/gshadow to 0000. I'm assuming this has been done for better security, so this script makes sure RHEL 6 has these permissions.

 - Created GEN000000-LNX00240.sh for RHEL 6 to document the manual check and change the fil esystem from ext3 to ext4.

 - Created GEN000000-LNX00360.sh for RHEL 6. Newer version of gnome have disabled the ability to change Xorg command line arguments through gdm.  The audit and auth entries are hard coded and correct. This script sets the idle_delay option to 15 minutes for the screensaver.

 - Created GEN000000-LNX00380.sh for RHEL 6.  Newer version of gnome have disabled the ability to change Xorg command line arguments through gdm.  The -ac -core and -nolock options are not hard  coded into gdm by default, so these shouldn't be a problem.


